recommend check-in only for the literal keystroke Keaton alone can supply -- running ./tools/hawm0_boot_onpath_host.sh from a plain terminal on this Framework host (not this jailed Cursor session). Everything upstream of that one command is real, verified, and done; the script's own GREEN/RED close will name plainly whether the AVD actually boots to a real Android 16 userland under KVM.
